column4: I need help, My entire applications menu is blank and menu editor won't open. How do I fix this?
How do i reset the panel?
Now there's no panel at all
you need to restart gnome ctrl + alt + f1 then sudo  /etc/init.d/gdm restart
it reset the menu but the applications folder is blank.
how did your panel get messed up in the first place?
are you using jaunty or what distro?
ok try this it will delete all the .conf files and reinstall them to default ctrl+alt+f1 again then sudo rm -rf .gnome .gnome2 .gconf .gconfd .metacity then /etc/init.d/gdm start
where are the config files localed? sry about questions i've only had ubuntu for a month.
should be /etc/init.d/gdm restart they are in ~/ or /home/yournamehere/
